
README for HeaderDoc

HeaderDoc is a text processing engine designed to pull specially-formatted
comments out of source code and header files.

HeaderDoc comes pre-installed in Mac OS X.  If you are installing on a
non-Mac OS X computer, or if you are installing an updated version of
HeaderDoc on a Mac OS X computer, you can quickly install by simply typing:

	make
	sudo make realinstall

For additional documentation on HeaderDoc, look at the HTML files in the
Documentation directory and at the man pages for gatherheaderdoc and
headerdoc2html.

If you encounter bugs or installation problems, send email to the
headerdoc-dev mailing list on lists.apple.com.
